e the ultimate integration involves all stakeholders of our system. It’s not only developers (the typical IDE fails today even on that front - for example, it fails every time the developer has to go on Stackoverflow to ask a question about her/his own system).\n\nTo reach this integration, the IDE has to offer these projections. As different aspects of our system are interesting from different perspectives, the IDE cannot rely on one single form. It must be moldable. I believe this is fundamental. By molding the way we perceive the internals of our systems, we can bring explainability into our specification and make it accessible to a wider audience.",
